Text.Value: We're just working towards a common goal. Don't get sentimental.
How are you feeling?
We should get some rest. Good night.
Keep this up, and I'm out of here.
Hmmm... you'd do well where I'm from. But don't try it again.
Wise... though I hope you'd miss me after I'm gone. I think I would, if the positions were reversed.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node only plays if SH approves of the player for 10 or more
EditorData.NodeContext: Approving of player's practical answer. Hint of affection towards them also.

Text.Value: I just want to know how you really feel.
Ah... that sounds... interesting. But on second thought, I'm quite tired.
Let's not do this. I don't like hypothetical questions.
I hope not. I'd miss our little conversations... wouldn't you miss them as well?
How about a few songs around the fire with the others?
I'm glad. Hopefully we can eke out some more time together, before all's done and dusted...
But you're right - if we're to make it through all this, there can be no room for hesitation. You're doing well.
It's a beautiful night. I think I'll stay up to enjoy it while I still can. Rest well.
It's a beautiful night. I think I'll stay up to enjoy it while I still can. Rest well.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Glancing up at the night sky.

Text.Value: Do that again, and I'll split your skull, understand?
Adventurous.
Oh. In that case, I won't keep you from your blanket. The time in my company will pass more quickly if you're asleep. Good night.
If I want you to know something, I'll tell you.
Just an observation.
The leader of the pack comes to chat.

EditorData.logicalname: Second night, talk to Shadowheart subsequently

Text.Value: *She is serious. Even she seems surprised. She's attracted to you...*
*You find a current of hope flowing through her thoughts. She believes you all have a real chance.*
Hah! And I'd chase you as fast as my tentacles could carry me.
Perhaps something else will come to you, before we part ways. Rest well.
Journey's not over yet. We should both get some rest.
Change the subject.
Do what again? What are you talking about?
Finally, some good fortune. Come morning, we know what to do.

EditorData.logicalname: Second night, talk to Shadowheart first

Text.Value: Besides, I can't afford to tire you out - we still have work to do. Rest well.
I hadn't thought of that. What do you have in mind?
I have enjoyed your company, yes.
Maybe I could leave you tied up while I hunted for a cure.
You're funny.
What are you doing...? Stop!

EditorData.NodeContext: Sharp anger. The player stepped over a boundary (tried to read her thoughts).

Text.Value: We'll need that kind of thinking to make it through all this. You're doing well.
Let a girl have some secrets. Was there anything else?
The sooner we part ways, the better. Until then, keep away from me.
Once this is all over, we should find a tavern and celebrate properly.
Now go rest. And keep your mind to yourself.
Yes, vastly so. But I don't want to talk about her. Not right now.
The same. These parasites are proving suspiciously benign.
Probably wise to just get some rest.
Really? I'd just kill you.
I can't wait to get this thing out of my head.
Is she serious? Probe her thoughts using your shared connection.
I hope so. Good night.
The sooner we find this 'Priestess Gut', the better. I can't wait to get rid of this thing in my head.
Use your shared connection. Probe her thoughts.
What's on your mind? You must be pleased to have a clear path forward.
No. I just want to put all this behind me.
But suppose I turn... what would you do?
No hesitations. I'd just end your misery, then and there.
The sooner we find the druid Halsin, the better. I can't wait to get rid of this thing in my head.
...but let's take care of our problem first. Rest well.
Head to Baldur's Gate. Someone's waiting for me.
I can't trust you, can I?
Oh yes? Who?
I had to be sure I could still trust you.
*... but you sense more - a warm swell of embarrassment.*
If you turned into a monster? I'd run away.
We should get some rest. Good night.
Perhaps we should wait for more comfortable surrounds.
A firm answer. I'd do the same.
You know, this could be our last night together.
Now leave me alone.
Disappointing.
At least you're honest. Don't do that again.
So what will come next for you, once this is all over?
We could find somewhere discreet right now... away from the camp.
Stop! I already warned you not to do that again.
It's hardly hypothetical - we're still in danger, after all.
This person in Baldur's Gate must be very important to you.
Heh. A little comfort and company doesn't sound bad...
Ah, this cursed thing!

EditorData.NodeContext: Cursed thing = tadpole. Player's attempted mindmeld caused her some discomfort.

Text.Value: *She's anxious to find this person in Baldur's Gate. Whoever it is has a strong hold over her, and can give her something she desperately wants...*
I'm sorry. I couldn't resist.
Hmmm... Brambles on bare skin aren't as fun in practice, I'm afraid.
Anyway, get some rest. Try not to dream about tying me up.
That's not something I'm accused of very often... but I suppose you're right. I'll let you get your rest - good night.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little surprised, but she can't fault the player's lack of sentiment.

Synopsis: Shadowheart confides in the player during the third night that they stop to camp. The expected effects of their tadpole condition have not come to pass, and Shadowheart tries to reason what this might mean. Are they out of the woods, or is this still just the start of something much worse? Hope and disquiet in equal parts.
